The paper presents a low-cost robotic racecar platform for education and research, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The platform also includes demos and lab assignments for hands-on experience, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). The platform is designed for multi-agent systems, which could be related to multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper emphasizes the educational aspect of the platform, which could be related to computer science education (cs.EDU).
